title.label: Doesn‚Äôt even have all ikea inventory.

content.label: So, firstly had to subscribe. Then, once purchasing, set dimensions of room and went to go add furniture. Mind you I was going to be purchasing only ikea furniture for my office, but the app doesn‚Äôt event have a large portion of Ikea inventory to even add! What a COMPLETE waste of money. Corner desks missing, whole collections. Getting my money back.

When the free version of an app is so crippled that it‚Äôs unusable, there effectively is no free version. The App Store listing says you can purchase Basic for 9.99 but that option isn‚Äôt available in the app itself. Instead, you‚Äôre constantly nagged to purchase a subscription. I prefer paying a flat price for an app, not being billed constantly and so I refuse to buy subscriptions. Especially for an app like this where they are essentially advertising furniture for purchase. Talk about double dipping! I‚Äôm sure IKEA pays the developer something to advertise their stuff and he charges us for the software every week/month/year. I believe developers deserve to earn a living, but $5/week is over $250/year.
